🏗️ Scenario: 3-Tier Web Application on AWS using Terraform
❓ Interview Question

“Design and implement a highly available 3-tier architecture in AWS using Terraform.”

✅ ✅ High-Level Architecture
🌐 Components:
Presentation Layer (Web Tier)
ALB (Application Load Balancer)
EC2 (Auto Scaling Group)
Application Layer (App Tier)
Private EC2 instances
Database Layer (DB Tier)
RDS (MySQL/PostgreSQL)
📊 Architecture Diagram (Textual)
Internet
   ↓
ALB (Public Subnet)
   ↓
Web Tier EC2 (Public Subnet / ASG)
   ↓
App Tier EC2 (Private Subnet)
   ↓
RDS (Private Subnet)
🔐 Networking (VPC Design)
📌 You explain like this in interview:
Create a VPC
2 AZs for High Availability
Subnets:
Public Subnets → ALB + Bastion
Private Subnets → App + DB
Terraform Example (VPC)
resource "aws_vpc" "main" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
}
Subnets
resource "aws_subnet" "public" {
  vpc_id     = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block = "10.0.1.0/24"
}
⚖️ Load Balancer (Web Tier Entry)
resource "aws_lb" "alb" {
  name               = "app-alb"
  load_balancer_type = "application"
  subnets            = [aws_subnet.public.id]
}

👉 Explain:

Routes traffic to Web Tier
Health checks enabled
🚀 Web Tier (Auto Scaling Group)
resource "aws_launch_template" "web" {
  image_id      = "ami-123"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}
resource "aws_autoscaling_group" "web_asg" {
  desired_capacity = 2
  max_size         = 4
  min_size         = 2
}

👉 Explain:

Auto scaling ensures availability
Deployed in multiple AZs
🔒 App Tier (Private EC2)
resource "aws_instance" "app" {
  ami           = "ami-123"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
  subnet_id     = aws_subnet.private.id
}

👉 Explain:

No public IP
Only accessible from Web Tier
🛢️ Database Tier (RDS)
resource "aws_db_instance" "db" {
  engine         = "mysql"
  instance_class = "db.t3.micro"
  allocated_storage = 20
  username       = "admin"
  password       = var.db_password
}

👉 Explain:

Deployed in private subnet
Multi-AZ enabled (important!)
🔐 Security Groups (VERY IMPORTANT)
Web SG:
Allow HTTP from Internet
App SG:
Allow traffic only from Web SG
DB SG:
Allow only from App SG
ingress {
  from_port   = 3306
  to_port     = 3306
  security_groups = [aws_security_group.app.id]
}
🔑 Bastion Host (Optional but interview favorite)

👉 Used to SSH into private instances

💾 Remote Backend (MUST MENTION)
